
- NodeJS is the Server Side Scripting Language.

- By using NodeJS , We Can Create HTTP & TCP Servers.

- As a Node Developer, we can assign the port numbers to the server.

Modules in NodeJS.

1. mysql
    - used to connect with the mysql database.

2.mongodb
    - used to connect to mongodb


3. express
    - used to develop the REST API.


4. body-parser
     - used to set the MIME Type

Ex.

     json

     xml

     text

     doc

     docx


5. jwt-simple
     - used to maintain the token based Authentication System.


6. http
     - used to create the http servers.


7. fs
     - used to interact with the file system

     Ex.

        static text files
        static xml files
        static json files
